    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-28T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860D.00/1029: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-28T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 28, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1275. Chief of Protocol<note n="8" xml:id="d128fn8">R. Hakkarainen.</note> last
                    night informed me that although annual New Year reception would not be held at
                    President’s Palace on January 1, it was expected that President’s book would be
                    signed by diplomatic representatives and that “pf”<note n="9" xml:id="d128fn9">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pro forma</hi>.</note> cards would be sent to Prime
                    Minister and Foreign Minister.</p>
                <p>In view of Japanese tea party on December 8, I am not disposed to send cards to
                    Rangell or Witting unless instructed to do so by you.<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d128fn10">No indication has been found in Department files of
                        instructions sent in this matter.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
